                            <comment id="17632639" author="olegk" created="Sat, 12 Nov 2022 09:42:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The pattern &lt;b&gt;&amp;#42;.compute-1.amazonaws.com&lt;/b&gt; is present in the Public Suffix List &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;. Therefore I have to assume &lt;b&gt;ec2.compute-1.amazonaws.com&lt;/b&gt; is expected to represent a domain, not a host.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;somehost.ec2.compute-1.amazonaws.com&lt;/b&gt; should match the pattern but &lt;b&gt;ec2.compute-1.amazonaws.com&lt;/b&gt; should not because It is not a host.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oleg&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://publicsuffix.org/list/public_suffix_list.dat&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://publicsuffix.org/list/public_suffix_list.dat&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
