                            <comment id="17633449" author="JIRAUSER298371" created="Mon, 14 Nov 2022 02:13:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=olegk&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;olegk&quot;&gt;olegk&lt;/a&gt; , &lt;b&gt;ec2.compute-1.amazonaws.com is the hostname in US-east-1 in reality. Please refer to &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/vpc-dns.html#vpc-dns-hostnames.&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://docs.aws.amazon.com/vpc/latest/userguide/vpc-dns.html#vpc-dns-hostnames.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&#160; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&quot;A public (external) IPv4 DNS hostname takes the form&#160;&lt;tt&gt;ec2-&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;public-ipv4-address&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;.compute-1.amazonaws.com&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;for the&#160;&lt;tt&gt;us-east-1&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;Region, and&#160;&lt;tt&gt;ec2-&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;public-ipv4-address&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;.&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;region&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;tt&gt;.compute.amazonaws.com&lt;/tt&gt; for other Regions.&quot;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Also wants to call out is that the issue does not exist in 4.5.3.&#160; I understand the matcher has been changed since then. But I still believe it is one issue of HTTPClient.&lt;/b&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17633677" author="olegk" created="Mon, 14 Nov 2022 10:44:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Also wants to call out is that the issue does not exist in 4.5.3.  I understand the matcher has been changed since then. But I still believe it is one issue of HTTPClient. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=chen2&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;chen2&quot;&gt;chen2&lt;/a&gt; The matcher algorithm has not changed. Feel free to take a look at the Git history or compare the code of the two branches. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What has changed is the public domain suffix list. Please approach Amazon for clarifications as to how interpret the following entry in the public domain suffix list&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;// Amazon EC2
// Submitted by Luke Wells &amp;lt;psl-maintainers@amazon.com&amp;gt;
// Reference: 4c38fa71-58ac-4768-99e5-689c1767e537
*.compute.amazonaws.com
*.compute-1.amazonaws.com
*.compute.amazonaws.com.cn
us-east-1.amazonaws.com
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oleg&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
